item.description: "Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic." -- Arthur C. Clarke

item.title: Darth add a quote by Rick Cook
item.description: "Programming today is a race between software engineers striving to build bigger and better idiot-proof programs, and the Universe trying to produce bigger and better idiots. So far, the Universe is winning." -- Rick Cook

item.title: Darth add a quote by George Carlin
item.description: "I tried to believe that there is a God, who created each of us in His own image and likeness, loves us very much, and keeps a close eye on things. I really tried to believe that, but I gotta tell you, the longer you live, the more you look around, the more you realize, something is fucked up." -- George Carlin

item.title: Darth add a quote by Robert Heinlein
item.description: "Apparently Blank thinks I am a nice accommodating guy, please explain to him that I am a son of a bitch" -- Robert Heinlein
